node.text:
Italian Moto GP rider @andreaiannone spotted wearing the latest emerald green @geraldcharles_official Maestro GC3.0 in 18k rose gold ✨

It features a chronograph with three counters for seconds, minutes and hours and is powered by an hand finished ultra-thin automatic chronograph movement called GCA3022/12 made by Vaucher.

Limited Edition to just 25 pieces worldwide and priced at $43,000

#GeraldCharles #geraldgenta

node.text:
The "La Montoya" is a collaboration between @ArtisansdeGeneve and F1 former driver Juan Pablo Montoya to produce a skeleton version of his favorite watch. Almost every part of the base watch has been enhanced, making this an exceptional timepiece to own.

This personalization was requested by a private client. Artisans de Genève is not affiliated nor authorized by Rolex SA.
〰️
📸 @watchcollecting_

node.text:
@luxewatches with the AP Royal Oak Jumbo Extra Thin in Rose Gold 👀✨
How do you like it?

The collaboration between @jacobandco x @alecmonopoly ✌🏼

The recently announced partnership between the internationally renowned contemporary graffiti artist, Alec Monopoly, and the luxury watch and jewelry brand, Jacob & Co., has resulted in the release of the first collaborative timepiece: The Astronomia Alec Monopoly.

The watch features miniature pop characters and images that are staples of Monopoly’s artwork within the iconic Astronomia four-arm vertical movement and its exclusive complications.

The painting of the characters with acrylic colors on such a small scale was among the most challenging works of the prolific street artist

Limited Edition of 9 pieces with a price tag of $600,000 💸

node.text:
Three new sapphire case versions of the @jacobandco x @bugatti Twin Turbo Furious 👀

A horological machine packed with complications such as double triple-axis sequential high-speed tourbillons, monopush chronograph, minute repeater and a power reserve indicator 👌🏼

It is the first watch in the history of haute horlogerie to place a decimal minute repeater inside a fully sapphire crystal case, which took approximately 15 months to design and produce.
